This paper is about improving the performance of an algorithm for solving imperfect-information games, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses a specific algorithm for game-solving. The paper also mentions game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) as related fields. Additionally, the algorithm involves pruning actions, which is a technique commonly used in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the algorithm, which is a topic that falls under control theory (cs.SY).
